searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"LibRaw","doc":"Native camera RAW decoding for the BEAM via a Rustler NIF wrapping libraw.","ref":"LibRaw.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Prerequisites - LibRaw","doc":"libraw must be installed on the system:\n\n    # macOS\n    brew install libraw\n\n    # Debian / Ubuntu\n    apt install libraw-dev","ref":"LibRaw.html#module-prerequisites"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - LibRaw","doc":"{:ok, image} = LibRaw.decode(\"/path/to/photo.CR3\")\n    # => %{pixels: <<...>>, width: 6000, height: 4000, colors: 3, bps: 8}\n\n    {:ok, meta} = LibRaw.metadata(\"/path/to/photo.CR3\")\n    # => %{camera_make: \"Canon\", camera_model: \"EOS R5\", iso: 400.0, ...}","ref":"LibRaw.html#module-examples"},{"type":"type","title":"LibRaw.decode_opts/0","doc":"","ref":"LibRaw.html#t:decode_opts/0"},{"type":"type","title":"LibRaw.image/0","doc":"","ref":"LibRaw.html#t:image/0"},{"type":"type","title":"LibRaw.metadata/0","doc":"","ref":"LibRaw.html#t:metadata/0"},{"type":"function","title":"LibRaw.decode/2","doc":"Decode a RAW image file, returning processed pixel data.\n\nRuns the full libraw pipeline: open тЖТ unpack тЖТ dcraw_process тЖТ\nin-memory bitmap. The NIF call is dispatched to a Dirty CPU scheduler\nbecause decoding typically takes 100тАУ500 ms.","ref":"LibRaw.html#decode/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - LibRaw.decode/2","doc":"* `path` тАФ `Path.t()`. Filesystem path to a camera RAW file. Passed\n    to libraw verbatim; non-ASCII paths work because the NIF takes a\n    UTF-8 binary, not a charlist.\n  * `opts` тАФ keyword list. See *Options* below.","ref":"LibRaw.html#decode/2-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - LibRaw.decode/2","doc":"* `:use_camera_wb` тАФ use the white balance stored in the file\n    (default: `true`).\n  * `:no_auto_bright` тАФ disable libraw's automatic brightening\n    (default: `false`).\n  * `:output_bps` тАФ bits per sample, either `8` or `16`\n    (default: `8`). Other values return `{:error, {:invalid_output_bps, n}}`\n    without touching the NIF.\n  * `:gamma` тАФ gamma curve: `:srgb`, `:linear`, or a `{g0, g1}` tuple\n    of numbers (default: `:srgb`). Anything else returns\n    `{:error, {:invalid_gamma, term}}`.","ref":"LibRaw.html#decode/2-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - LibRaw.decode/2","doc":"* `{:ok, image}` тАФ `image` is a map with the keys:\n    * `:pixels` тАФ raw pixel bytes as a binary, row-major, interleaved\n      per channel.\n    * `:width` / `:height` тАФ pixel dimensions.\n    * `:colors` тАФ channel count (typically `3` for RGB).\n    * `:bps` тАФ bits per sample, matches `:output_bps`.\n  * `{:error, reason}` тАФ option-validation failures (see *Options*),\n    a libraw error string for unsupported / corrupted files, or\n    `\"invalid path: contains null byte\"` for paths containing `\\0`.","ref":"LibRaw.html#decode/2-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"LibRaw.metadata/1","doc":"Read EXIF metadata from a RAW image file without running the full\ndecode pipeline.\n\nOnly `libraw_open_file` is called, so this is dramatically cheaper\nthan `decode/2` тАФ typically single-digit milliseconds. Still\nscheduled on a Dirty CPU scheduler because the open touches disk.","ref":"LibRaw.html#metadata/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - LibRaw.metadata/1","doc":"* `path` тАФ `Path.t()`. Filesystem path to a camera RAW file.","ref":"LibRaw.html#metadata/1-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - LibRaw.metadata/1","doc":"* `{:ok, metadata}` тАФ `metadata` is a map with the keys:\n    * `:camera_make` тАФ manufacturer name (e.g. `\"Canon\"`).\n    * `:camera_model` тАФ model name (e.g. `\"EOS R5\"`).\n    * `:captured_at` тАФ `DateTime` in UTC, or `nil` if libraw\n      reports no shooting timestamp (returns `0` from libraw).\n    * `:iso` тАФ ISO speed as a float.\n    * `:shutter` тАФ shutter speed in seconds as a float (e.g. `0.004`\n      for 1/250s).\n    * `:aperture` тАФ f-number as a float.\n    * `:orientation` тАФ EXIF orientation / flip code as an integer.\n  * `{:error, reason}` тАФ a libraw error string for unsupported /\n    corrupted files, or `\"invalid path: contains null byte\"`.","ref":"LibRaw.html#metadata/1-returns"},{"type":"extras","title":"LibRaw","doc":"# LibRaw\n\nAn Elixir library for native camera RAW decoding on the BEAM, powered by a\n[Rustler](https://github.com/rusterlium/rustler) NIF that wraps\n[libraw](https://www.libraw.org/).","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Prerequisites - LibRaw","doc":"libraw must be installed before compiling or running `:libraw`:\n\n```bash\n# macOS\nbrew install libraw\n\n# Debian / Ubuntu\napt install libraw-dev\n```\n\n> **LGPL compliance:** libraw is dynamically linked at runtime. Distributing\n> your application requires that end users can replace the libraw shared\n> library. See the [libraw license](https://www.libraw.org/license) for\n> details.","ref":"readme.html#prerequisites"},{"type":"extras","title":"Installation - LibRaw","doc":"Add `:libraw` to your `mix.exs` dependencies:\n\n```elixir\ndef deps do\n  [\n    {:libraw, \"~> 0.1\"}\n  ]\nend\n```","ref":"readme.html#installation"},{"type":"extras","title":"Usage - LibRaw","doc":"","ref":"readme.html#usage"},{"type":"extras","title":"Decode a RAW file - LibRaw","doc":"```elixir\n{:ok, image} = LibRaw.decode(\"/path/to/photo.CR3\")\n# => %{pixels: <<...>>, width: 6000, height: 4000, colors: 3, bps: 8}\n\n# 16-bit output with linear gamma\n{:ok, image16} = LibRaw.decode(\"/path/to/photo.CR3\",\n  output_bps: 16,\n  gamma: :linear\n)\n\n# Custom gamma curve\n{:ok, image_custom} = LibRaw.decode(\"/path/to/photo.NEF\",\n  gamma: {2.4, 12.92},\n  use_camera_wb: true,\n  no_auto_bright: true\n)\n```\n\n#### Options\n\n| Option           | Type                            | Default  | Description                              |\n|------------------|---------------------------------|----------|------------------------------------------|\n| `use_camera_wb`  | `boolean`                       | `true`   | Use white balance stored in the file     |\n| `no_auto_bright` | `boolean`                       | `false`  | Disable automatic brightening            |\n| `output_bps`     | `8 \\| 16`                      | `8`      | Bits per sample in the output            |\n| `gamma`          | `:srgb \\| :linear \\| {g0, g1}` | `:srgb`  | Gamma curve                              |\n\n#### Return value\n\n```elixir\n%{\n  pixels: binary(),         # raw pixel bytes (interleaved RGB or RGBA)\n  width:  non_neg_integer(),\n  height: non_neg_integer(),\n  colors: non_neg_integer(), # number of color channels (typically 3)\n  bps:    non_neg_integer()  # bits per sample of the output\n}\n```","ref":"readme.html#decode-a-raw-file"},{"type":"extras","title":"Read metadata without decoding - LibRaw","doc":"```elixir\n{:ok, meta} = LibRaw.metadata(\"/path/to/photo.CR3\")\n# => %{\n#      camera_make:  \"Canon\",\n#      camera_model: \"EOS R5\",\n#      captured_at:  ~U[2023-06-15 10:32:11Z],  # DateTime UTC, or nil\n#      iso:          400.0,\n#      shutter:      0.002,                        # seconds\n#      aperture:     2.8,                          # f-number\n#      orientation:  0                             # EXIF flip code\n#    }\n```","ref":"readme.html#read-metadata-without-decoding"},{"type":"extras","title":"Architecture - LibRaw","doc":"```\nlib/\n  lib_raw.ex          Public API: decode/2, metadata/1, gamma resolution, timestamp parsing\n  lib_raw/\n    nif.ex            use Rustler + NIF stubs (nif_not_loaded fallbacks)\nnative/\n  libraw_nif/\n    Cargo.toml        deps: rustler = \"0.33\"; build-deps: cc = \"1\", pkg-config = \"0.3\"\n    build.rs          pkg_config::probe(\"libraw\") for dynamic linking; cc::Build compiles wrapper.c\n    src/\n      lib.rs          rustler::init! and two #[rustler::nif(schedule = \"DirtyCpu\")] functions\n      wrapper.c       thin C shim тАФ C compiler resolves all struct field offsets\n      raw.rs          safe Rust RAII wrappers around libraw_data_t / libraw_processed_image_t\n      error.rs        LibRawError enum + helpers\n```","ref":"readme.html#architecture"},{"type":"extras","title":"Why a C shim? - LibRaw","doc":"Direct bindgen / libraw-sys approaches embed struct field offsets at compile\ntime, which can break across libraw versions 0.20, 0.21, and 0.22 as the\nstruct layout evolves.  `wrapper.c` is compiled with the same headers as the\ninstalled libraw, so the C compiler always uses the correct offsets.  Rust\ncalls only opaque C functions and never touches libraw structs directly.","ref":"readme.html#why-a-c-shim"},{"type":"extras","title":"Dirty CPU Schedulers - LibRaw","doc":"Both NIFs (`decode_nif` and `metadata_nif`) are annotated with\n`schedule = \"DirtyCpu\"`.  Decoding a RAW file typically takes 100тАУ500 ms,\nwhich is far beyond the 1 ms NIF time budget for normal schedulers.  Running\non dirty schedulers prevents blocking the BEAM scheduler threads.","ref":"readme.html#dirty-cpu-schedulers"},{"type":"extras","title":"License - LibRaw","doc":"MIT тАФ see [LICENSE](LICENSE).","ref":"readme.html#license"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.1"}}